  <script>
    function buildPaymentPage() {
      // Create HTML elements for the payment page
      const p=document.getElementById("p");
      const paymentPage = document.createElement('div');
      paymentPage.innerHTML = `
        <h2>Payment Information</h2>
        <form id="paymentForm">
          <label for="cardNumber">Card Number:</label>
          <input type="text" id="cardNumber" name="cardNumber" required><br>
          
          <label for="expiryDate">Expiry Date:</label>
          <input type="text" id="expiryDate" name="expiryDate" placeholder="MM/YY" required><br>
          
          <label for="cvv">CVV:</label>
          <input type="text" id="cvv" name="cvv" required><br>
          
          <button type="button" onclick="processPayment()">Submit Payment</button>
        </form>
      `;

      // Append the payment page to the body
      document.getElementById("p").appendChild(paymentPage);
    }

    function processPayment() {
      // Implement your payment processing logic here
      // For simplicity, let's just show an alert for now
      alert('Payment processed successfully!');
      
      // Redirect to the confirmation page
      window.location.href = 'confirmation.html';
    }
  </script>
